ican Americans and Native Americans (see also 5 below).","Irish and Scottish: adopted for <b>Ó Duinn</b> (see   Dunn  ) or for any of the many Irish and Scottish Gaelic names containing the element <i>donn</i> ‘brown-haired’ (also meaning ‘chieftain’), for example   Donahue  .","Irish: phonetic Anglicization of <b>Mac an Bhreitheamhnaigh</b>; see   Breheny  ."]}]},{"name":"Euphame","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Scottish: A female name found in Scotland, the same as Euphame; or from sv well, and at,ivw, to appear."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Euphame Broun was born about 1606, in Edinburgh, Scotland, her father, Robert Broun, was 22 and her mother, Katherine Douglas, was 18. She had at least 1 daughter with Thomas Craig."},"et":{"about 1606–":"umbes 1606–Surnud","1604–1645":"1604–1645","1606–Female":"1606–Surnud","1602–Male":"1602–Surnud","1600–Male":"1600–Surnud","1625–Male":"1625–Surnud","1626–1680":"1626–1680","1629–Male":"1629–Surnud","1633–Female":"1633–Surnud","1585–Male":"1585–Surnud","1590–Female":"1590–Surnud","10 Apr 1625":"10. aprill 1625","1680":"1680","1590":"1590","19 Apr 1633":"19. aprill 1633","about 1606":"umbes 1606","1602":"1602","1645":"1645","1633":"1633","1600":"1600","1585":"1585","21 May 1626":"21. mai 1626","1629":"1629","1606":"1606","20 Sep 1629":"20. september 1629","1626":"1626","1604":"1604","1625":"1625","Edinburgh, Midlothian, Scotland":"Edinburgh, Scotland","EDINBURGH PARISH, EDINBURGH, MIDLOTHIAN, SCOTLAND":"Edinburgh, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Edinburgh Parish, Edinburgh, Midlothian, Scotland":"Edinburgh, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1606–":"noin 1606–Kuollut","1604–1645":"1604–1645","1606–Female":"1606–Kuollut","1602–Male":"1602–Kuollut","1600–Male":"1600–Kuollut","1625–Male":"1625–Kuollut","1626–1680":"1626–1680","1629–Male":"1629–Kuollut","1633–Female":"1633–Kuollut","1585–Male":"1585–Kuollut","1590–Female":"1590–Kuollut","10 Apr 1625":"10. huhtikuuta 1625","16